At the time of the nominating convention in 1888, Mr. Blaine was in Europe, and by formal letter declined to permit his friends to present his name as a candidate for the presidency. He returned, however, in time to aid efficiently in the canvass for Mr. Harrison, and on the elec- tion of the latter again accepted the appointment as Secretary of State.
